OL,3,CWhy has Mary Poppins' UK age rating
OL,4,Cbeen raised?
OL,6,FThe original version of the film has
OL,7,Fbeen changed from a U rating to PG
OL,8,Frating because it contains
OL,9,F"discriminatory language".
OL,11,FThe British Board of Film
OL,12,FClassification (BBFC) has reviewed the
OL,13,F1964 classic over the use of the word
OL,14,F"Hottentots" - a term now considered
OL,15,Fracially offensive.
OL,17,FIn the film, Admiral Boom - played by
OL,18,Factor Reginald Owen - uses the word
OL,19,Fwhen he asks one of the children if
OL,20,Fthey were going to "fight the
OL,21,FHottentots".
