OL,3,CWhy has Mary Poppins' UK age rating
OL,4,Cbeen raised?
OL,6,FThe word Hottenton refers to the
OL,7,FKhoekhoe, the indigenous people of
OL,8,FSouth Africa and Namibia. It was
OL,9,Finitially coined by Dutch settlers who
OL,10,Farrived in the region in 1650s.
OL,12,FWhile the etymology of the word has
OL,13,Fnever been established, it is widely
OL,14,Fassumed to be linked to a Dutch phrase
OL,15,Ffor stutter, applied to the Khoekhoe
OL,16,Fon account of the distinctive click
OL,17,Fconsonants in their languages.JThe
OL,18,Fword had entered English usage in the
OL,19,F17th century.
