OL,3,CWhy has Mary Poppins' UK age rating
OL,4,Cbeen raised?
OL,6,FIn earlier usage of the word,
OL,7,FHottentot was a term used to denote
OL,8,Fall Black people or as a reference
OL,9,Fspecifically to the Khoekhoe people.
OL,11,FHowever, from the 18th century onwards
OL,12,Fit was used as a term of abuse,
OL,13,Fcomparable to barbarian.
OL,15,FIn modern language, the reduced form
OL,16,F"hotnot" has also been borrowed into
OL,17,FSouth African English as a derogatory
OL,18,Fterm for Black people.
