OL,3,CWhy has Mary Poppins' UK age rating
OL,4,Cbeen raised?
OL,6,FA BBFC spokesperson told ITV News:
OL,7,F"While Mary Poppins has a historical
OL,8,Fcontext, the use of discriminatory
OL,9,Flanguage is not condemned, and
OL,10,Fultimately exceeds our guidelines for
OL,11,Facceptable language at U. We therefore
OL,12,Fclassified the film PG for
OL,13,Fdiscriminatory language.
