OL,3,CWhy has Mary Poppins' UK age rating
OL,4,Cbeen raised?
OL,6,FAs British audience attitudes shift,
OL,7,Fit has become necessary to reclassify
OL,8,Ffilms according to the latest
OL,9,Fguidelines.
OL,11,FThe BBFC consults the public every
OL,12,Ffour years to establish a standard of
OL,13,Facceptability in which it holds the
OL,14,Findustry to.
OL,16,FFor this reason, if the distributor of
OL,17,Fa film hopes to see it re-released in
OL,18,Fcinemas - as in the case of Mary
OL,19,FPoppins - it needs to be reviewed by
OL,20,Fthe BBFC.
